The paper deals with the relationship between rewards, utility, and information, which are all concepts that are commonly studied in computer science. The paper's focus on probability distributions and entropy suggests that it belongs to the Information Theory (cs.IT) category. However, the paper also discusses the application of these concepts to agent-environment interactions, which is a common topic in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
